OL,3,CMan arrested for allegedly spitting at
OL,4,Cpolice during Donaldson court hearing
OL,6,FChief Superintendent Mervyn Seffen
OL,7,Fsaid: "There was a large media
OL,8,Fpresence, alongside a smaller number
OL,9,Fof members of the public, who at
OL,10,Ftimes, were pushing and shoving our
OL,11,Fofficers to get closer to the
OL,12,Fdefendants.J"One of our officers was
OL,13,Falso spat at by a 37-year-old man, who
OL,14,Fwas a bystanding member of the public.
OL,15,FHe was arrested later that day,
OL,16,FWednesday 24th April, for assault on
OL,17,Fpolice. He has since been released
OL,18,Fpending further enquiries.J"We
OL,19,Fappreciate the high profile nature of
OL,20,Fthis case but always ask that our
OL,21,Fofficers, who are on the ground to
OL,22,Fkeep people safe, are treated with
OL,23,Frespect."
